trans-unit.source: A young man picks up a blue iPod nano.
You see him flip it over and smile when he discovers the built-in video camera.
As he places it down, he leans over to look at the specifications on the iPod nano sign on the table.
Think of two approaches you could use for this customer.
{5}Note: {6}You can practice these approaches later with a Mentor.
Personalize your approach to the customer.
Your goal is to start a conversation.
{8}Ask peers to demonstrate their favorite iPod nano approaches.
Commit to observing customers and their body language every day.

trans-unit.source: To help customers make the right choices, we need to educate them about these misconceptions.
The battery is not replaceable, so when it dies you have to buy a new iPod.
You cannot see your photos on iPod nano.
Remember that when a customer says these things, they are actually voicing a needa need that they mistakenly believe iPod nano cannot fulfill.

trans-unit.source: To present iPod nano as a viable solution for a customers needs, take the following steps:
Ask questions to fully understand the need
Assure customer that iPod nano can fulfill the need
Present a solution that fulfills the need
Let the customer test-drive iPod nano and directly experience how it can meet their needs
After you resolve all concerns and present a compelling solution, what comes next?

Strive to remember the names of five customers that you help today.

trans-unit.source: Tara wants to buy a new iPod.
She has the following specific needs:
She wants to stay within a budget of about $150 USD.
She wants to handle her own service and support without any out-of-pocket repair costs.
She now takes the train to work, and she misses the morning radio shows she listened to in her car.
In the Notes section to the left, write down your answers to the following questions:
What open-ended questions could you ask Tara to discover the needs mentioned above?
What products would you present to address Taras needs?
Which features of those products would you demonstrate?
